# UI Component and Icon Standard

- Use `shadcn-ui` as the default source for UI components.
- Use `lucide-react` as the default icon library.
- Prefer composition with `shadcn-ui` primitives before building custom components from scratch.
- When adding missing UI dependencies, use `pnpm` commands.

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Good
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Plus } from "lucide-react";

export function CreateButton() {
  return (
    <Button>
      <Plus className="mr-2 h-4 w-4" />
      Create
    </Button>
  );
}
```

```tsx
// ❌ Avoid introducing alternate component/icon libraries by default
import { Button } from "@mui/material";
import { FiPlus } from "react-icons/fi";
```

```bash
# ✅ Use pnpm for installs
pnpm add lucide-react
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button
```
